These threads are managed by user-level libraries instead of the operating system kernel.

Characteristics:
Managed in user space
OS is not aware of these threads
Faster creation and switching
Implemented by thread libraries

Advantages:
✔ Fast thread management
✔ No kernel involvement
✔ Efficient switching

Disadvantages:
✘ If one thread blocks, entire process may block
✘ Cannot take full advantage of multi-core CPUs

Examples:
User thread libraries used in systems like POSIX Threads (Pthreads).
